cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a method for building sentence representations for natural language processing tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also mentions that their approach is non-parameterized, which suggests that it may fall under the category of unsupervised learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper uses pre-trained word embeddings, which is a common technique in deep learning (cs.AI). The paper also mentions evaluating their approach on downstream tasks, which suggests that it may fall under the category of applied machine learning (cs.CV) or neural networks (cs.NE).
